ygData.messageBody:
Hmm, the tutorial mod program wasn't well written at all, imho.

However, I'm looking for a different program that *supposedly* allowed
people to extract spell information from one of the .DLL files

hrmph...

-----Original Message-----
From: Sam Powell [mailto:sam@ti.l-3com.com]
Sent: Monday, November 08, 1999 11:27 AM
To: EQCheats@onelist.com
Subject: Re: [EQCheats] EQ Viewer


From: Sam Powell <sam@ti.l-3com.com>


If this is the program that lets you load any zone into the tutorial, then
yes, I've seen it. Don't have any links but you can try the files section
at eq stratics. It's a bit grainy and doesn't let you go into full screen
mode, but it does work. It's always daylight and sunny in whatever zone
you load (try it with a dark zone like kithicor, it's pretty funny!). I
used it a couple months ago to check out the plane of hate.

Word of warning tho. It messed up my install, had to reinstall EQ
afterwards.
